Read State package

some times we have to write duplicate logic!
like we want to develop photoshop app, we have a pallet of tools on left side
and our canvas behave differently (canvas is class to provides a drawing surface)
if we use different tools (it turn to brush, eraser, selector,...)

so our canvas obj will response to mouse event like
press and release mouse button
this action do something based on selected tools
so we need a long If/Else or Case/When statement on it!
and we need repeat these conditions all over the App
(like long conditions we have in shadab)

    public void mouseDown(){
        if(currentTool == ToolType.SELECTION)
            System.out.println("selection icon");
        else if (currentTool == ToolType.BRUSH)
            System.out.println("brush icon");
        else if (currentTool == ToolType.ERASER)
            System.out.println("eraser icon");
    }

    public void mouseUp(){
        if(currentTool == ToolType.SELECTION)
            System.out.println("draw dashed rectangle");
        else if (currentTool == ToolType.BRUSH)
            System.out.println("draw a line");
        else if (currentTool == ToolType.ERASER)
            System.out.println("eraser something");
    }


Note: in real draw application we have more tool (longer conditions)
      more actions (more methods)
      so this approach is not "maintainable"
      we have lack of "extensibility" (if we add a tool, we should change all conditions!)
      so we have to develop a canvas method some how not depend on tool!
      we can use OOP to solve this problem!
